<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="82" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1255,2037]" pageId="1" pageNumber="82">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,273,1255,1280]" pageId="1" pageNumber="82">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
The male of 
<taxonomicName box="[430,579,1256,1279]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Colletes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="82" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="comaticus">
<emphasis box="[430,579,1256,1279]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="82">C. comaticus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a characteristically shaped S 
<number box="[957,971,1256,1280]" pageId="1" pageNumber="82" value="7.0">7</number>
(
<figureCitation box="[989,1054,1255,1280]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1757,1779]" captionTargetBox="[152,1435,193,1732]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,193,1736]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Colletes comaticus Kuhlmann, sp. nov., male: a. specimen, lateral view; b. gonostylus (lateral view); c. metasomal sternum 7 (dorsal view). C. bernadettae Kuhlmann 2000, male: d. metasomal sternum 7 (dorsal view). C. comatus Noskiewicz 1936, male: e. metasomal sternum 7 (dorsal view). C. comatoides Kuhlmann &amp; Proshchalykin 2013, male: f. metasomal sternum 7 (dorsal view). Scale bar: 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/239795/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="82">
Fig. 
<number box="[1043,1054,1256,1280]" pageId="1" pageNumber="82" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
c) that is apically much narrower than in the closely related 
<taxonomicName authority="Kuhlmann" authorityName="Kuhlmann" box="[444,736,1292,1317]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Colletes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="82" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bernadettae">
<emphasis box="[444,611,1292,1316]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="82">C. bernadettae</emphasis>
Kuhlmann
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[751,814,1292,1317]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1757,1779]" captionTargetBox="[152,1435,193,1732]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,193,1736]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Colletes comaticus Kuhlmann, sp. nov., male: a. specimen, lateral view; b. gonostylus (lateral view); c. metasomal sternum 7 (dorsal view). C. bernadettae Kuhlmann 2000, male: d. metasomal sternum 7 (dorsal view). C. comatus Noskiewicz 1936, male: e. metasomal sternum 7 (dorsal view). C. comatoides Kuhlmann &amp; Proshchalykin 2013, male: f. metasomal sternum 7 (dorsal view). Scale bar: 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/239795/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="82">
Fig. 
<number box="[803,814,1292,1317]" pageId="1" pageNumber="82" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
d) and 
<taxonomicName authority="Kuhlmann &amp; Proshchalykin" authorityName="Kuhlmann &amp; Proshchalykin" box="[895,1375,1292,1317]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Colletes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="82" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="comatoides">
<emphasis box="[895,1055,1292,1316]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="82">C. comatoides</emphasis>
Kuhlmann &amp; Proshchalykin
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1757,1779]" captionTargetBox="[152,1435,193,1732]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,193,1736]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Colletes comaticus Kuhlmann, sp. nov., male: a. specimen, lateral view; b. gonostylus (lateral view); c. metasomal sternum 7 (dorsal view). C. bernadettae Kuhlmann 2000, male: d. metasomal sternum 7 (dorsal view). C. comatus Noskiewicz 1936, male: e. metasomal sternum 7 (dorsal view). C. comatoides Kuhlmann &amp; Proshchalykin 2013, male: f. metasomal sternum 7 (dorsal view). Scale bar: 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/239795/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="82">
Fig. 
<number box="[151,162,1327,1352]" pageId="1" pageNumber="82" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
f). In 
<taxonomicName authority="Noskiewicz" authorityName="Noskiewicz" box="[231,500,1327,1352]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Colletes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="82" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="comatus">
<emphasis box="[231,359,1328,1352]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="82">C. comatus</emphasis>
Noskiewicz
</taxonomicName>
the apical emargination of S 
<number box="[831,845,1328,1352]" pageId="1" pageNumber="82" value="7.0">7</number>
is shallower and it has numerous lateral hairs at its base (
<figureCitation box="[218,283,1364,1389]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1757,1779]" captionTargetBox="[152,1435,193,1732]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,193,1736]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Colletes comaticus Kuhlmann, sp. nov., male: a. specimen, lateral view; b. gonostylus (lateral view); c. metasomal sternum 7 (dorsal view). C. bernadettae Kuhlmann 2000, male: d. metasomal sternum 7 (dorsal view). C. comatus Noskiewicz 1936, male: e. metasomal sternum 7 (dorsal view). C. comatoides Kuhlmann &amp; Proshchalykin 2013, male: f. metasomal sternum 7 (dorsal view). Scale bar: 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/239795/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="82">
Fig. 
<number box="[272,283,1364,1388]" pageId="1" pageNumber="82" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
e) that are lacking in 
<taxonomicName box="[533,682,1364,1388]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Colletes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="82" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="comaticus">
<emphasis box="[533,682,1364,1388]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="82">C. comaticus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Furthermore, T 
<number box="[872,885,1365,1388]" pageId="1" pageNumber="82" value="7.0">7</number>
is apically shallowly emarginate (
<figureCitation box="[1279,1347,1364,1389]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1845,1867]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,303,1822]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,303,1822]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Colletes comaticus Kuhlmann, sp. nov., male: a. metasomal terga 1 and 2; b. metasomal tergum 7. C. bernadettae Kuhlmann 2000, male: c. metasomal terga 1 and 2; d. metasomal tergum 7. C. comatoides Kuhlmann &amp; Proshchalykin 2013, male: e. metasomal terga 1 and 2; f. metasomal tergum 7. Scale bar: 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/239796/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="82">
Fig. 
<number box="[1333,1347,1364,1389]" pageId="1" pageNumber="82" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
b) in 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Colletes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="82" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="comaticus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="82">C. comaticus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(similar in 
<taxonomicName box="[413,545,1400,1424]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Colletes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="82" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="comatus">
<emphasis box="[413,545,1400,1424]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="82">C. comatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) while 
<taxonomicName box="[644,817,1400,1424]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Colletes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="82" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bernadettae">
<emphasis box="[644,817,1400,1424]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="82">C. bernadettae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[838,911,1399,1424]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1845,1867]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,303,1822]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,303,1822]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Colletes comaticus Kuhlmann, sp. nov., male: a. metasomal terga 1 and 2; b. metasomal tergum 7. C. bernadettae Kuhlmann 2000, male: c. metasomal terga 1 and 2; d. metasomal tergum 7. C. comatoides Kuhlmann &amp; Proshchalykin 2013, male: e. metasomal terga 1 and 2; f. metasomal tergum 7. Scale bar: 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/239796/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="82">
Fig. 
<number box="[897,911,1399,1424]" pageId="1" pageNumber="82" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
d) and 
<taxonomicName box="[1001,1167,1400,1424]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Colletes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="82" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="comatoides">
<emphasis box="[1001,1167,1400,1424]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="82">C. comatoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[1189,1262,1399,1424]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1845,1867]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,303,1822]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,303,1822]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Colletes comaticus Kuhlmann, sp. nov., male: a. metasomal terga 1 and 2; b. metasomal tergum 7. C. bernadettae Kuhlmann 2000, male: c. metasomal terga 1 and 2; d. metasomal tergum 7. C. comatoides Kuhlmann &amp; Proshchalykin 2013, male: e. metasomal terga 1 and 2; f. metasomal tergum 7. Scale bar: 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/239796/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="82">
Fig. 
<number box="[1248,1262,1399,1424]" pageId="1" pageNumber="82" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
f) have clearly developed spines. The disc of T 
<number box="[507,521,1436,1460]" pageId="1" pageNumber="82" value="2.0">2</number>
is almost completely covered with short appressed hairs in 
<taxonomicName box="[1187,1333,1436,1460]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Colletes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="82" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="comaticus">
<emphasis box="[1187,1333,1436,1460]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="82">C. comaticus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[1348,1414,1436,1461]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1845,1867]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,303,1822]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,303,1822]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Colletes comaticus Kuhlmann, sp. nov., male: a. metasomal terga 1 and 2; b. metasomal tergum 7. C. bernadettae Kuhlmann 2000, male: c. metasomal terga 1 and 2; d. metasomal tergum 7. C. comatoides Kuhlmann &amp; Proshchalykin 2013, male: e. metasomal terga 1 and 2; f. metasomal tergum 7. Scale bar: 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/239796/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="82">
Fig. 
<number box="[1400,1414,1436,1460]" pageId="1" pageNumber="82" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
a) and 
<taxonomicName box="[201,329,1472,1496]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Colletes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="82" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="comatus">
<emphasis box="[201,329,1472,1496]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="82">C. comatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
while in 
<taxonomicName box="[442,611,1472,1496]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Colletes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="82" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bernadettae">
<emphasis box="[442,611,1472,1496]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="82">C. bernadettae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[629,699,1471,1496]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1845,1867]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,303,1822]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,303,1822]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Colletes comaticus Kuhlmann, sp. nov., male: a. metasomal terga 1 and 2; b. metasomal tergum 7. C. bernadettae Kuhlmann 2000, male: c. metasomal terga 1 and 2; d. metasomal tergum 7. C. comatoides Kuhlmann &amp; Proshchalykin 2013, male: e. metasomal terga 1 and 2; f. metasomal tergum 7. Scale bar: 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/239796/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="82">
Fig. 
<number box="[684,699,1472,1496]" pageId="1" pageNumber="82" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
c) and 
<taxonomicName box="[779,942,1472,1496]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Colletes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="82" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="comatoides">
<emphasis box="[779,942,1472,1496]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="82">C. comatoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[960,1029,1471,1496]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1845,1867]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,303,1822]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,303,1822]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Colletes comaticus Kuhlmann, sp. nov., male: a. metasomal terga 1 and 2; b. metasomal tergum 7. C. bernadettae Kuhlmann 2000, male: c. metasomal terga 1 and 2; d. metasomal tergum 7. C. comatoides Kuhlmann &amp; Proshchalykin 2013, male: e. metasomal terga 1 and 2; f. metasomal tergum 7. Scale bar: 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/239796/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="82">
Fig. 
<number box="[1014,1029,1472,1496]" pageId="1" pageNumber="82" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
e) the disc is glabrous to a variable extend. The punctation on the disc of T 
<number box="[595,605,1508,1532]" pageId="1" pageNumber="82" value="1.0">1</number>
is coarser, more dispersed and shiny between punctures in 
<taxonomicName box="[1269,1436,1508,1532]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Colletes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="82" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bernadettae">
<emphasis box="[1269,1436,1508,1532]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="82">C. bernadettae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
than in the three other species who have very fine and dense punctation.
</paragraph>
